nglish <i>Ducc(a)</i>, but was more often a pet form of <i>Marmaduke</i>, especially in Yorkshire (see   Duke  ). <i>Marmaduke</i> itself is from Irish <i>Maol Maedóc</i> ‘servant of Maedóc’, <i>Maedóc</i> being the name of prominent Irish saints of the 6th and 7th centuries."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Doggett was born in 1445, in Sudbury, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Robert Lappage."},"et":{"1445–":"1445–Surnud","1445–Male":"1445–Surnud","1463–Female":"1463–Surnud","1445–Female":"1445–Surnud","1445":"1445","1463":"1463","Groton, Sudbury, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Graton,Sudbury,Suffolk,England.":"Sudbury, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1445–":"1445–Kuollut","1445–Male":"1445–Kuollut","1463–Female":"1463–Kuollut","1445–Female":"1445–Kuollut","1445":"1445","1463":"1463","Groton, Sudbury, Suffolk, England":"Groton, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Graton,Sudbury,Suffolk,England.":"Sudbury, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1445–":"1445–Décédée","1445–Male":"1445–Décédé","1463–Female":"1463–Décédée","1445–Female":"1